race.comment: SEA ME DANCE (10) has progressed nicely since arriving in the Marcus Wilson stable this prep. Made a sustained run from before the corner to get up for second last start over 1590m at Ballina. Ready to win out to this trip at the third run back. SETHFIRE (4) produced a real eye-catcher when fresh from a spell over 1509m at Port Macquarie last time out, chiming in late to be beaten under a length. That race has thrown up three subsequent winners to add to the merit of the performance. Will be tough to hold out. ELITE DELIGHT (9) appreciated a step back from provincial grade when a barnstorming second over 1650m at Moruya recently. Very fit mare who should be in the finish again. SHARE TRADER (11) led and was just overhauled by subsequent winner Icewater at Ballina last start. Progressive three-year-old who should give a great sight. TURPIN'S TORMENT (5) has raced here at this trip twice for two minor placings so he cannot be left out.
